cafes.name: The Catcade - Cat Cafe & Rescue
cafes.address: 624 W Belmont Ave, Chicago, IL 60657, USA

text.text: This was and is the best experience I‚Äôve ever had at a ‚Äúcat cafe‚Äù! The staff was so welcoming, friendly, and you could tell how much they love those cats & kittens in there and how they know each and everyone by name & their personalities. The space was perfect and I had the best hour & a half with all these cats. It was an instant serotonin booster! Highly highly recommend coming here. I fell in love with two kitty sisters that I instantly put an application in for while on the bus back home. Go visit and donate to these kitties in need!

To be honest, it was a little bit underwhelming. I am probably saying that because I already have cats at home, so I‚Äôm probably thinking ‚Äú I could‚Äôve just pet my cats at home for free‚Äù haha.
The staff was nice, the cats were adorable, my wife and I had a great time.
With your visit, you get a a soft beverage included, and you can just have a relaxing time with some cats.
I was pretty impressed with how great they were with cleaning up every hour so that the next group could have a clean visit.
I personally wouldn‚Äôt do it again, but I am glad that my money supports a cat adoption center, and it was worth trying at least once.

I think this is going to be a 5 star experience for cat lovers. I have many in my life and have been to a few cat cafe experiences with them. I enjoyed the novelty that the Catcade offered where you're in an arcade setting rather than a cafe one.

Staff were friendly. Experience well organized. There were even kittens running around.

cafes.name: Tree House Cat Cafe (Reserve your spot today!)
cafes.address: 7225 N Western Ave, Chicago, IL 60645, USA

text.text:
I had a wonderful experience at the cat caf√©! Big Bear, the resident cat, is an absolute sweetheart‚Äîaffectionate and adorable. He loves being petted and enjoys weaving through your legs. Also he played with us while in his bed, as you can see in the video.

The hot chocolate and tea we ordered were perfect, making our visit even more enjoyable. The Tree House Humane Society‚Äôs facilities are well-organized, and it‚Äôs clear they genuinely care about the well-being of their cats. We had such a great time and would definitely visit again!
Had a lovely visit with the one cat in the cafe (the rest were adopted! üòª) and got to chill, read, and color while sipping on the included coffee. $10 entry for a good cause!
I absolutely love this place and if you like cats you would love it as well. Downside Is you can only sit with the cats for 30 minutes but 10/10

cafes.name: The Cat House
cafes.address: 344 Irving Park Rd, Roselle, IL 60172, USA

text.text: Visiting the new Cat House is a must if you‚Äôre a cat lover in the suburbs. It‚Äôs a lot of fun and you definitely won‚Äôt be bored when you‚Äôre here, plenty of kitties walking around, playing or sleeping. There‚Äôs also educational materials, books, and games and you can also purchase cat-themed merchandise. A lot of photo opportunities! The place is clean and doesn‚Äôt have an odor. I would definitely come back again soon.

This place is amazing. I wanted to adopt all the cats. The staff is wonderful. It is very clean. And talk about therapeutic getting to spend 45 minutes with the fur babies. It's a fantastic experience!!

Update: I adopted my first kitten from here!!! Amazing experience, staff was very kind and we managed to get everything done the same day since I already applied for a different cat a week prior. Her name at the house was Noah, a little midnight sweetheart, we now renamed her to Koi. Thank you again heartland and cat house!

Amazing experience that is a higher quality than the cafes in Chicago. No screaming kids harassing cats and very relaxing atmosphere and experience. Staff was attentive and very experienced. Thank you for the great time!

cafes.name: Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 346 Irving Park Rd, Roselle, IL 60172, USA

text.text: Despite my allergies to cats, it was an awesome experience. My kids loved it. We plan on coming back regularly. To the comments that said it smelled bad, the smell is close to what you‚Äôd expect with a shelter, it didn‚Äôt bother us since we expected it. It‚Äôs a small place with lots of kitties it won‚Äôt smell like a coffee shop!

People need to understand and respect that cats are each unique just like any body and any animal else-wise.   There is a certain time of day they are sleepy and nappy.   May not always want to be stimulated and playful, that‚Äôs ok.  I had a blast as I am in-between situations and just left a home with a pet and feeling lonely.  The cafe seem to be very successful in finding homes for cats and the cats are good to find their own space.  You pay for initial hour(45mins?) and can buy a treat or drink to enjoy while you‚Äôre there.  There are cafe merch and many lovely items cat-related (obvs) to buy.  If I wasn‚Äôt already overwhelmed with the desire to want a cat and been shopping already today, would def buy merch/trinkets next time.  15/10.  May become a regular.üôÉüíöüíöüíö

I brought my older daughters, 10 and 12 and it was nice for them.  But the under 15 years needs to be supervised seems a bit absurd.  It‚Äôs a short wall that separates the waiting area from the cats.  I didn‚Äôt have any interest and didn‚Äôt feel like I should pay sit on the other side of the wallüòí When I can easily supervise from the waiting area.

Felt like more of a money grab, than a necessity.

cafes.name: The Cat's Meow Caf√©
cafes.address: 507 N Hershey Rd, Bloomington, IL 61704, USA

text.text: I'm a regular at this cafe. There's tons of cats, the prices are very reasonable, and the coffee is delicious (I'm not usually a coffee drinker, but their coffee is always perfect). It's very clear these cats live very happily. There's almost no smell whatsoever, and it's always kept very clean given the amount of cats. The staff are also all very friendly and wonderful people. I love coming here.

Second time we've been here. Love this place! The cats are adorable and playful. The drinks are nice to sip while petting a kitty! Staff are friendly and attentive to the cats. The cats are well kept. If you love cats I can't recommend this place enough!

First of all: No upcharge for alternative milks!! What a nice cat cafe to curl up with some kitties! It‚Äôs always a good time to enjoy a cup of and watch the cats playing, sleeping, etc. knowing they are well loved here. I am glad to see they had forms to sign before entering, for the safety of everyone and cats.

It was a quiet morning when we came in, so we had the chance to interact with many cats with different personalities. The entry fee is very inexpensive for the time you get as well as the included drink discount, and I enjoyed the ‚Äòconstant comment‚Äô bag tea & small donut I got. I felt the experience was worth more than I had to pay, and I love that this place happily supports these cats‚Äô needs. My friend from LA was impressed. Friendly, personable staff. I will be back!

cafes.name: River Kitty Cafe
cafes.address: 3226 N University St, Peoria, IL 61604, USA

text.text:
This place was absolutely perfect! The environment is so cozy, relaxing, and extremely clean! All the kittens & cats are super friendly, adorable and very social with everyone. My partner and I ordered a Cherry Lemonade & Iced Coffee and they were delicious!

Not to mention the price for admission, beverages, and even gifts are incredibly fair! You really can't complain there - and even the fellow customers were very respectful of everyone. So, this place is definitely worth a visit! You never know, you might bring a baby home too! üêæ

Needed some coffee and just happened to be near River Kitty cafe so decided to stop in for the first time. Upon walking in, I noticed that it was a bit small, not many tables for sitting if you didn't want to be in the room with the cats. If I remember correctly, there was only two tables, and then there were bar stools where you could sit and watch the cats through the glass. I noticed there was about nine people or so in the room where the cats were and they were just sitting around and enjoying the company. The cats were very comfortable and some were taking a nap, but you can tell that they enjoy the visits. I feel that it was a little bit odd of a layout for example it was a coffee shop and it seemed like the area for the coffee was very small. I also think that adding some warm tones of paint like maybe tan walls and one burgundy accent wall, that would really make the space more inviting and comfortable. The room was divided with a closed door where the cats stayed, but quite understandably there would have to be a door that way the cats wouldn't run out when the door opened. It was $6 for a half an hour and $12 for 1 hour to sit with the cats.
The young man at the counter was very polite and took my order for my latte. The coffee was good but the syrup pretty much stayed settled at the bottom of the cup. However, it got the job done, and I got the energy that I needed to get through the afternoon. If I'm in the area I'll probably stop back by and grab another coffee.

This was a pretty cool place! Helps locals have something nice to do while also helping the local population of stray and surrender cats. It‚Äôs nice that you can get some coffee and spend some time around cats if someone in your household is allergic or your apartment doesn‚Äôt allow pets.

The only concern I had was that some of the kids kept forcing kittens into situations that they weren‚Äôt comfortable with. Some of the cats maybe need break times they can take away from the kids to rest a bit.

All in all, this place is still a big net positive for the community, and I hope they remain here for many years to come.

cafes.name: The Cats' Pyjamas Cat Caf√©
cafes.address: 524 E Capitol Ave, Springfield, IL 62701, USA

text.text:
My kids (7 and 12) had such a great time here! The owner is very friendly, gave us a tour, introduced us to all of the residents, and told us about each cat. Most of them love to interact with people, and we fell in love with a couple kitties.

There‚Äôs local brewed coffee and hot chocolate, super cute cat sugar cookies, and a gift shop with handmade catnip toys (video of my cat enjoying them!). It‚Äôs easier for me to visit a cat cafe over a shelter, because they all look so happy to be there. I made an appointment online which was super easy. Definitely give this place a visit!

My friend and I came here, and we had such a great time with the kitties! I wish we could've taken them all home! The Cafe was so cute and had a lot of space to play with the cats. The cats were so sweet and adorable. The owner was also very helpful and answered any questions we had. We'll definitely be back with more friends. I hope this place helps a lot of cats find their forever homes!

We went right as they opened, and it was a great experience üëå  Hopscotch was our Lil buddy during our session. Clean and calm. It was exactly what we needed to unplug for an hour. We have dogs at home and don't have an option to own a cat, so we very much appreciate the opportunity üòÄ

This is a great way to get to meet the adoption cats. Great little place staff is very friendly, so we're the cats and kittens if you recently lost your fur family  member. This is a place where you can meet the cat or cats and play with them. Lunch was good. I highly recommend  stopping by  it will ease the loss of your fur family member, but also comfort you in adopting  the next fur family member to make new memories with. Stop in

We drove an hour and fifteen minutes to visit this very nice cat cafe. My expectations were surpassed big time. The staff, food and drink, and of course the main purpose the best kittens and cats you‚Äôve ever seen and played with. We had a great time. This place does not smell like chemicals and pet poop. It feels like you are visiting a cat spa. If its soul purpose is to help you forget your troubles then it worked. We did not go to adopt, we went to see the kitties. Sometimes you go to places and you feel like ‚Äú been there done that‚Äù I feel the opposite. This will be on my list of staycations every year. We each had some very tasty coffee and pastries before we hung out with our new furry friends. Some great things I noticed.
1. The cats wear collars. Our cat will not wear a collar because she never got used to it. Important for identification in case your cat gets lost.
2. No pushy sales, Not once did someone try to guilt us into adopting.
3. Every cat or kitten is around other cats and kittens. So if we decide to adopt down the road we know the issue with your pet and your new cat should go smooth as can be.
Sorry about this long review but this place is damn near perfect.

What an adorable place! Everywhere you look is cat themed sayings on the wall or cat decor on the tables... but so well put together and not tacky! I want to try every drink and every food item because it all sounds delicious.  (Nutty pumpkin latte? Yes please!) Upstairs you can view the cats from a birds eye view and play cat themed games or look through cat themed books.

If you want to pet the kitties it's $11/pp and is for 50 minutes with entry at the top of the hour (10 ppl at a time). We'll definitely be back for that sometime.

So glad we got to come visit.  We were out this way and happen to be looking for a place to sit down for a cup of coffee.

Wish Google would include them when searching coffee though... it doesn't come up and is the best in the area for a great cup of joe!

cafes.name: MeowTown
cafes.address: 301 W Elm St, Alton, IL 62002, USA

text.text:
Was great being able to play with the cats! They're well taken care of, the place is clean, lots of toys and glad the cats have a place to escape to when they're just not wanting to interact.
The cookies were really good. More options would be awesome though.

When you leave and go "oh no, I shouldn't have talked so much," you know the vibes are right. Amazing energy and the cutest (mostly) ADOPTABLE cats!

Edit: mostly is because there is one forever cat, so mostly adoptable not mostly cute!

This place was truly impressive!!! I got so excited to see something like this coming to our area! We need more places like this. The people were kind and welcoming and the cats were also! Had I not just adopted the two we have, I would have definitely taken one (or two) home. The cafe is warm and inviting and well-organized. I cannot wait to go back one day! Thank you for bringing such an amazing place to our area!

My friend and I made an appointment to visit on a Saturday afternoon. When we arrived, we were greeted immediately. As this was our first visit, we were given a brief orientation. After ordering our drinks, we went in to meet the kitties. It was a fun hour of petting cats and swapping stories about our own pets with others. When we left, my friend and I agreed that we both felt less stressed and more relaxed than we had been. We'll definitely visit again.

Visited from Chicago and decided to stop by because who doesn't love cats and the coffee is a bonus! No, but seriously the staff was super friendly and I love that they take care of the cats. The cookie I got was really good and so was my iced chai. Pretty affordable too! The cats were all super cute and overall it was a fun experience.

A really lovely place to visit if you‚Äôre a cat person! The staff here are very friendly and attentive, both to you and the cats. It‚Äôs clear that they genuinely care about the happiness of every cat living here.

The cats are adorable, each with their own unique personality. Some are especially affectionate and will completely melt your heart!

The price is affordable‚Äî$12 includes admission and a selection of drinks, such as iced tea or coffee, at no extra cost. However, some specialty drinks require an additional fee. It would be even better if visitors could stay longer than an hour!

This makes the pricing explanation clearer and aligns with what you want to convey.

cafes.name: The Kitty Crib
cafes.address: 3113 N Market St, Champaign, IL 61822, USA

text.text: Our team has recently spent a few hours volunteering at The Kitty Crib. We spent our time helping where we were needed and getting to know the amazing cats and incredible staff here. We cannot sing enough praises for these wonderful ladies; Kim, Donna, and Emily have created a calm and enticing atmosphere for both the customers and the cats. If you are looking for a fun new hangout with some cool cats, the Kitty Crib is definitely the place to check out.
Kitties are super adorable and nice! Even the workers were so kind! I went here for the first time and had an amazing experience. Definitely will go again! üòä

Had a great time at the Kitty Crib‚Äôs Valentines Day event! All the kitties were such cuties and the employees even handed out gift bags! I would definitely recommend visiting for a calming kitty experience.

cafes.name: Kitty Hawk Cafe
cafes.address: 2700 International Dr, West Chicago, IL 60185, USA

text.text: Need to go whole grain! Nice place to stop for food and fuel if you are flying. Nice place to drive to, grab lunch, and watch planes if you are on the ground in the area. The food is good but could really use a whole-grain make-over. Whole wheat sandwiches please!
I'm not sure who these whole wheat clowns are that are commenting... But do your thing.
It's nice to be able to get a nice sandwich & chips at the airport FBO, but if you aren't pressed for time, i have to recommend Portillos.

Great goodness!! We reserved a spot right at 11, and for just a $10 reservation, we enjoyed up to an hour with the cats. From the moment we walked in, we were greeted by the sweetest cats and kittens. A delightful staff member joined us, sharing her knowledge about the adoption process and each cat in her care. It was the perfect midday break! We left with the same number of cats we arrived with‚Äîmuch to my husband‚Äôs relief.

If you‚Äôve been thinking about going but haven‚Äôt yet, do it! You won‚Äôt regret it. üêà  üêà‚Äç‚¨õÔ∏è

Enjoying life 1 sip, 1 bite, and 1 small town at a time! Explore everything!

love, Love, LOVE this place!! Visited from TN 8/17/24. Don't go in the late afternoon (2p-5p) because the "kids"(cats) are sleeping. We went at 4p and the majority of them were asleep. üòü A couple stirred, don't wake them. You go in a few at a time and there are double doors to make sure you don't let the "kids" out. Reservations are required. They have bottles of wine to buy, magnets, smoothies, snacks, pop and toys for the "kids". They ranged in age from a year to a 8 years old and you could adopt on the spot! They are well-behaved and each is named with their own personality. Nice part is you can have a conversations with lovely people who are of like mind and love domesticated, loving little kings and queens of your jungle!üëëüêà‚Äç‚¨õüêàüòªüòΩ

The coffee was okay. The macarons were amazing! But the kitties were the highlight of the day! The guy monitoring the cat lounge was very helpful and informative.

I do wish, however, that young children were limited or even not allowed to be in the room without someone responsible watching them. It kind of put a damper on our visit to have them chasing the cats off and being aggressive with them. They got scratched and bitten several times because they do not understand how to approach cats and their parent did nothing to correct or control them. She actually encouraged them to bother specific cats that we were clearly spending time with. At least one of the cats was visibly stressed the whole time they were in the room. I was happy to see them leave!

That was obviously a parenting problem, but the staff do need to set some boundaries or constantly be in the room to discourage this type of behavior and/or remove people from the room when needed.

Overall, I would definitely visit again! Maybe I‚Äôll just pay for all 10 spots to make sure we have a calm and pleasant experience. üòâ
